data.enText: a precious stone that has been cut and polished and is used in jewellery

data.chText: 难能可贵的人；风景优美的地方；美妙绝伦的事物
data.enText: a person, place or thing that is especially good

data.chText: 这幅画是收藏中的极品。
data.enText: This picture is the gem (= the best) of the collection.

tr: art highly prized for its beauty or perfection
a precious or semiprecious stone incorporated into a piece of jewelry
a sweet quick bread baked in a cup-shaped pan
a person who is as brilliant and precious as a piece of jewelry
a crystalline rock that can be cut and polished for jewelry
example: he had the gem set in a ring for his wife
she had jewels made of all the rarest stones

value.def: A gem is a jewel or stone that is used in jewellery.

example.ex: ...a gold mask inset with emeralds and other gems.
example.tran: 一张镶有翡翠和其他宝石的金面具

value.def: If you describe something or someone as a gem, you mean that they are especially pleasing, good, or helpful.

example.ex: ...a gem of a hotel, Castel Clara...
example.tran: 卡斯特尔·克拉拉酒店，酒店中的明珠

example.ex: Miss Famous, as she was called, was a gem.
example.tran: “知名小姐”人如其名，是个尤物。

value.tran: 难能可贵的人（或物）；令人非常惬意的人（或事物）；精品
